				 Transfer looms on firing officer
																								Calcutta, Nov. 2: The third of the four police officers who ordered the March 14 firing in Nandigram is set to be transferred.																								Home secretary P.R. Ray today confirmed the decision to shift western range inspector-general Arun Gupta. His transfer proposal has come to us. It should happen next week.																								Arun Gupta will swap posts with inspector-general (administration) Rakesh Gupta.																								Earlier this week, the government transferred East Midnapore superintendent G.A. Srinivas and additional superintendent Tanmoy Roychowdhury, who had ordered the firing from the Bhangabera bridge. Debashish Boral, another additional superintendent posted in Nandigram that day, was also removed.																								The only officer from the firing squad still in his post is Midnapore range deputy inspector-general N. Ramesh Babu. 																								The transfers are believed to be a fallout of the governments negotiations with the Bhoomi Uchchhed Pratirodh Committee. 																								Prakash nod to paramilitary																								CPM general secretary Prakash Karat today endorsed the governments decision to send central forces to Nandigram. The chief ministers opinion is our partys stand. The prevailing situation in Nandigram cant be allowed to continue, Karat said. 
